      <hedline>
        <hl1>For Love of Process</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Barbara Michel letter holds David Thomson's September 17 article on movie Citizen Kane misses point that Orson Welles was revealed in process of making film rather than in story (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I think that David Thomson misses the point. ''Citizen Kane's'' pre-eminence has less to do with its subject than with its delirious love of the filmmaking process itself. If Orson Welles is revealed, it is in the process of making the film rather than in the story.</p>
        <p>BARBARA MICHEL  Toronto</p>
      </block>
